# Responsible for setting:
#   MMU_HAS_FILAMENT_BUFFER
#
# Whether MMU has loose filament catchment buffer. No options
#
# Can be disabled and forced off with:
#   select UNSELECT_MMU_HAS_FILAMENT_BUFFER


config UNSELECT_MMU_HAS_FILAMENT_BUFFER
  bool

if !UNSELECT_MMU_HAS_FILAMENT_BUFFER
  comment "_"
  comment "_Filament Catchment"

  config MMU_HAS_FILAMENT_BUFFER
    bool "Has filament buffer to catch loose filament?"
    forceshow
    default n
    help
      Does MMU have a buffer to catch the uncoiled filament on unload?
      Enabling this enabled a higher bowden load/unload speed when
      Happy Hare knows the filament is in the buffer rather than on the spool.
      Note: A passive rewinder like Filamentalist is not a filament buffer
      because it rewinds filament onto the spool!
      Obviously this is not required if you have an espooler.
endif
